sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_review_hub.ConnectAPI</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>Establishes the Rest API connection</description><name>ConnectAPI</name><script><![CDATA[var ConnectAPI = Class.create();
ConnectAPI.prototype = {
	
	response: {},
		
	initialize: function(type,restParam) {

		var buildNewRestMessage = function(type,restParam) {
			var restMessage = new sn_ws.RESTMessageV2(),
				result = {};
			var urlPattern = new RegExp(/https:\/\/(\w+)\.service\-now\.com\/api\/.*/g);

			restMessage.setHttpMethod(type);

			if (!restParam.hasOwnProperty("instance") || restParam.instance === "") {
				throw new Error(
					"Please specify instance name, this property is mandatory & cannot be undefined or empty"
				);
			}

			var getAuthenticationDetails = function(_instance) {
				
				/*var table_name = "x_snc_review_hub_instance";
				var field_name = "name";
				var _auth_data = {};
				var gr = new GlideRecord(table_name);
				gr.addQuery(field_name, restParam.instance);
				gr.query();
				if (gr.next()) {
					_auth_data.username = gr.user_name;
					_auth_data.password = gr.password.getDecryptedValue();
				}*/
                var _auth_data = {};
				var username = gs.getProperty('x_snc_review_hub.username');
				var password = gs.getProperty('x_snc_review_hub.password');
				
				_auth_data.username = username;
				_auth_data.password = password;
				return _auth_data;
			};

			var auth_data = getAuthenticationDetails(restParam.instance);
			restMessage.setBasicAuth(auth_data.username, auth_data.password);

			if (!restParam.hasOwnProperty("url") || restParam.url === "") {
				throw new Error(
					"Please specify valid URL, this property is mandatory & cannot be undefined or empty"
				);
			} else if (!urlPattern.test(restParam.url)) {
				throw new Error(
					"Please specify valid endpoint: https://<instance-name>.service-now.com/api/{path to scripted API}"
				);
			} else {
				restMessage.setEndpoint(restParam.url);
			}

			switch (type) {
				case "GET":
					if (
						restParam.hasOwnProperty("sysparm_query") &&
						restParam.sysparm_query != ""
					) {
						restMessage.setQueryParameter(
							"sysparm_query",
							restParam.sysparm_query
						);
					}

					if (
						restParam.hasOwnProperty("sysparm_fields") &&
						restParam.sysparm_fields != ""
					) {
						restMessage.setQueryParameter(
							"sysparm_fields",
							restParam.sysparm_fields
						);
					}

					if (
						restParam.hasOwnProperty("content_type") &&
						restParam.content_type != ""
					) {
						restMessage.setRequestHeader("Content-Type", restParam.content_type);
					}

					if (restParam.hasOwnProperty("accept") && restParam.accept != "") {
						restMessage.setRequestHeader("Accept", restParam.accept);
					}

					break;

				default:
					if (!restParam.hasOwnProperty("requestBody")) {
						throw new Error(
							"Please specify request Body for PUT/POST type of requests"
						);
					}

					restMessage.setRequestBody(restParam.requestBody);

					if (
						restParam.hasOwnProperty("content_type") &&
						restParam.content_type != ""
					) {
						restMessage.setRequestHeader("Content-Type", restParam.content_type);
					} else {
						restMessage.setRequestHeader("Content-Type", "application/json");
					}
					if (restParam.hasOwnProperty("accept") && restParam.accept != "") {
						restMessage.setRequestHeader("Accept", restParam.accept);
					} else {
						restMessage.setRequestHeader("Accept", "application/json");
					}
					break;
			}

			var _result = restMessage.execute();

			if (typeof _result != undefined && _result.getBody()) {
				result = {
					status: _result.getStatusCode()
				};
				if (!_result.haveError()) {
					result["response"] = _result.getBody();
				} else {
					result["error"] = {
						code: _result.getErrorCode(),
						message: _result.getErrorMessage(),
						body: _result.getBody()
					};
				}
			} else {
				result = null;
			}

			return result;
		};

		this.response = buildNewRestMessage(type,restParam);
	},


	type: "ConnectAPI"
};
				]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>souvik</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-01-09 12:16:18</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>3f2e33a9db230340a86a5404ce961997</sys_id><sys_mod_count>24</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ConnectAPI</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Review Hub" source="x_snc_review_hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Review Hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_3f2e33a9db230340a86a5404ce961997</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>haribabu.garbhana</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-05-18 10:20:15</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_review_hub.DmpDifferAPI</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>Internally Uses

Google's Diff Match and Patch

Copyright 2006 Google Inc.
http://code.google.com/p/google-diff-match-patch/

Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");
you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.
You may obtain a copy of the License at

http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software
distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,
WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.
See the License for the specific language governing permissions and
limitations under the License.
</description><name>DmpDifferAPI</name><script><![CDATA[var DmpDifferAPI = Class.create();
DmpDifferAPI.prototype = {
	
	// Defaults.
	// Redefine these in your program to override the defaults.
	
	// Number of seconds to map a diff before giving up (0 for infinity).
	Diff_Timeout: 0,
	// Cost of an empty edit operation in terms of edit characters.
	Diff_EditCost: 4,
	// At what point is no match declared (0.0 = perfection, 1.0 = very loose).
	Match_Threshold: 0.5,
	// How far to search for a match (0 = exact location, 1000+ = broad match).
	// A match this many characters away from the expected location will add
	// 1.0 to the score (0.0 is a perfect match).
	Match_Distance: 1000,
	// When deleting a large block of text (over ~64 characters), how close do
	// the contents have to be to match the expected contents. (0.0 = perfection,
	// 1.0 = very loose).  Note that Match_Threshold controls how closely the
	// end points of a delete need to match.
	Patch_DeleteThreshold: 0.5,
	// Chunk size for context length.
	Patch_Margin: 4,
	
	// The number of bits in an int.
	Match_MaxBits: 32,
	
	DIFF_DELETE: -1,
	DIFF_INSERT: 1,
	DIFF_EQUAL: 0,
	
	initialize: function(options) {
		for(var key in options){
			this[key] = options[key];
		}
	},
	diff_main: function(text1, text2, opt_checklines, opt_deadline){
		// Set a deadline by which time the diff must be complete.
		if (typeof opt_deadline == 'undefined') {
			if (this.Diff_Timeout <= 0) {
				opt_deadline = Number.MAX_VALUE;
			} else {
				opt_deadline = new Date().getTime() + this.Diff_Timeout * 1000;
			}
		}
		var deadline = opt_deadline;
		
		// Check for null inputs.
		if (text1 == null || text2 == null) {
			throw new Error('Null input. (diff_main)');
		}
		
		// Check for equality (speedup).
		if (text1 == text2) {
			if (text1) {
				return [[this.DIFF_EQUAL, text1]];
			}
			return [];
		}
		
		if (typeof opt_checklines == 'undefined') {
			opt_checklines = true;
		}
		var checklines = opt_checklines;
		
		// Trim off common prefix (speedup).
		var commonlength = this.diff_commonPrefix(text1, text2);
		var commonprefix = text1.substring(0, commonlength);
		text1 = text1.substring(commonlength);
		text2 = text2.substring(commonlength);
		
		// Trim off common suffix (speedup).
		commonlength = this.diff_commonSuffix(text1, text2);
		var commonsuffix = text1.substring(text1.length - commonlength);
		text1 = text1.substring(0, text1.length - commonlength);
		text2 = text2.substring(0, text2.length - commonlength);
		
		// Compute the diff on the middle block.
		var diffs = this.diff_compute_(text1, text2, checklines, deadline);
		
		// Restore the prefix and suffix.
		if (commonprefix) {
			diffs.unshift([this.DIFF_EQUAL, commonprefix]);
		}
		if (commonsuffix) {
			diffs.push([this.DIFF_EQUAL, commonsuffix]);
		}
		this.diff_cleanupMerge(diffs);
		return diffs;
	},
	
	/**
	 * Determine the common prefix of two strings.
	 * @param {string} text1 First string.
	 * @param {string} text2 Second string.
	 * @return {number} The number of characters common to the start of each
	 *     string.
	 */
	diff_commonPrefix: function(text1, text2) {
	  // Quick check for common null cases.
		if (!text1 || !text2 || text1.charAt(0) != text2.charAt(0)) {
			return 0;
		}
		// Binary search.
		// Performance analysis: http://neil.fraser.name/news/2007/10/09/
		var pointermin = 0;
		var pointermax = Math.min(text1.length, text2.length);
		var pointermid = pointermax;
		var pointerstart = 0;
		while (pointermin < pointermid) {
			if (text1.substring(pointerstart, pointermid) ==
				text2.substring(pointerstart, pointermid)) {
				pointermin = pointermid;
				pointerstart = pointermin;
			} else {
				pointermax = pointermid;
			}
			pointermid = Math.floor((pointermax - pointermin) / 2 + pointermin);
		}
		return pointermid;
	},


	/**
	 * Determine the common suffix of two strings.
	 * @param {string} text1 First string.
	 * @param {string} text2 Second string.
	 * @return {number} The number of characters common to the end of each string.
	 */
	diff_commonSuffix: function(text1, text2) {
	  // Quick check for common null cases.
	  if (!text1 || !text2 ||
		  text1.charAt(text1.length - 1) != text2.charAt(text2.length - 1)) {
		return 0;
	  }
	  // Binary search.
	  // Performance analysis: http://neil.fraser.name/news/2007/10/09/
	  var pointermin = 0;
	  var pointermax = Math.min(text1.length, text2.length);
	  var pointermid = pointermax;
	  var pointerend = 0;
	  while (pointermin < pointermid) {
		if (text1.substring(text1.length - pointermid, text1.length - pointerend) ==
			text2.substring(text2.length - pointermid, text2.length - pointerend)) {
		  pointermin = pointermid;
		  pointerend = pointermin;
		} else {
		  pointermax = pointermid;
		}
		pointermid = Math.floor((pointermax - pointermin) / 2 + pointermin);
	  }
	  return pointermid;
	},
	/**
	 * Find the differences between two texts.  Assumes that the texts do not
	 * have any common prefix or suffix.
	 * @param {string} text1 Old string to be diffed.
	 * @param {string} text2 New string to be diffed.
	 * @param {boolean} checklines Speedup flag.  If false, then don't run a
	 *     line-level diff first to identify the changed areas.
	 *     If true, then run a faster, slightly less optimal diff.
	 * @param {number} deadline Time when the diff should be complete by.
	 * @return {!Array.<!diff_match_patch.Diff>} Array of diff tuples.
	 * @private
	 */
	diff_compute_: function(text1, text2, checklines,
		deadline) {
	  var diffs;

	  if (!text1) {
		// Just add some text (speedup).
		return [[this.DIFF_INSERT, text2]];
	  }

	  if (!text2) {
		// Just delete some text (speedup).
		return [[this.DIFF_DELETE, text1]];
	  }

	  var longtext = text1.length > text2.length ? text1 : text2;
	  var shorttext = text1.length > text2.length ? text2 : text1;
	  var i = longtext.indexOf(shorttext);
	  if (i != -1) {
		// Shorter text is inside the longer text (speedup).
		diffs = [[this.DIFF_INSERT, longtext.substring(0, i)],
				 [this.DIFF_EQUAL, shorttext],
				 [this.DIFF_INSERT, longtext.substring(i + shorttext.length)]];
		// Swap insertions for deletions if diff is reversed.
		if (text1.length > text2.length) {
		  diffs[0][0] = diffs[2][0] = this.DIFF_DELETE;
		}
		return diffs;
	  }

	  if (shorttext.length == 1) {
		// Single character string.
		// After the previous speedup, the character can't be an equality.
		return [[this.DIFF_DELETE, text1], [this.DIFF_INSERT, text2]];
	  }

	  // Check to see if the problem can be split in two.
	  var hm = this.diff_halfMatch_(text1, text2);
	  if (hm) {
		// A half-match was found, sort out the return data.
		var text1_a = hm[0];
		var text1_b = hm[1];
		var text2_a = hm[2];
		var text2_b = hm[3];
		var mid_common = hm[4];
		// Send both pairs off for separate processing.
		var diffs_a = this.diff_main(text1_a, text2_a, checklines, deadline);
		var diffs_b = this.diff_main(text1_b, text2_b, checklines, deadline);
		// Merge the results.
		return diffs_a.concat([[this.DIFF_EQUAL, mid_common]], diffs_b);
	  }

	  if (checklines && text1.length > 100 && text2.length > 100) {
		return this.diff_lineMode_(text1, text2, deadline);
	  }

	  return this.diff_bisect_(text1, text2, deadline);
	},
	/**
	 * Do the two texts share a substring which is at least half the length of the
	 * longer text?
	 * This speedup can produce non-minimal diffs.
	 * @param {string} text1 First string.
	 * @param {string} text2 Second string.
	 * @return {Array.<string>} Five element Array, containing the prefix of
	 *     text1, the suffix of text1, the prefix of text2, the suffix of
	 *     text2 and the common middle.  Or null if there was no match.
	 * @private
	 */
	diff_halfMatch_: function(text1, text2) {
	  if (this.Diff_Timeout <= 0) {
		// Don't risk returning a non-optimal diff if we have unlimited time.
		return null;
	  }
	  var longtext = text1.length > text2.length ? text1 : text2;
	  var shorttext = text1.length > text2.length ? text2 : text1;
	  if (longtext.length < 4 || shorttext.length * 2 < longtext.length) {
		return null;  // Pointless.
	  }

		  k1_offset = v_offset + k1;

				 text1.charAt(x1) == text2.charAt(y1)) {

			x2 = v2[k2_offset + 1];

				 text2.charAt(text2_length - y2 - 1)) {

		  if (x2 > text1_length) {

		  } else if (y2 > text2_length) {

			  } else if (count_insert === 0) {

					count_delete + count_insert, [this.DIFF_DELETE, text_delete]);

		  }

		  if (diffs[pointer - 1][1] != bestEquality1) {
			// We have an improvement, save it back to the diff.
			if (bestEquality1) {
			  diffs[pointer - 1][1] = bestEquality1;
			} else {
			  diffs.splice(pointer - 1, 1);
			  pointer--;
			}
			diffs[pointer][1] = bestEdit;
			if (bestEquality2) {
			  diffs[pointer + 1][1] = bestEquality2;
			} else {
			  diffs.splice(pointer + 1, 1);
			  pointer--;
			}
		  }
		}
		pointer++;
	  }
	},
	/**
	 * Determine if the suffix of one string is the prefix of another.
	 * @param {string} text1 First string.
	 * @param {string} text2 Second string.
	 * @return {number} The number of characters common to the end of the first
	 *     string and the start of the second string.
	 * @private
	 */
	diff_commonOverlap_: function(text1, text2) {
	  // Cache the text lengths to prevent multiple calls.
	  var text1_length = text1.length;
	  var text2_length = text2.length;
	  // Eliminate the null case.
	  if (text1_length == 0 || text2_length == 0) {
		return 0;
	  }
	  // Truncate the longer string.
	  if (text1_length > text2_length) {
		text1 = text1.substring(text1_length - text2_length);
	  } else if (text1_length < text2_length) {
		text2 = text2.substring(0, text1_length);
	  }
	  var text_length = Math.min(text1_length, text2_length);
	  // Quick check for the worst case.
	  if (text1 == text2) {
		return text_length;
	  }

	  // Start by looking for a single character match
	  // and increase length until no match is found.
	  // Performance analysis: http://neil.fraser.name/news/2010/11/04/
	  var best = 0;
	  var length = 1;
	  while (true) {
		var pattern = text1.substring(text_length - length);
		var found = text2.indexOf(pattern);
		if (found == -1) {
		  return best;
		}
		length += found;
		if (found == 0 || text1.substring(text_length - length) ==
			text2.substring(0, length)) {
		  best = length;
		  length++;
		}
	  }
	},
	/**
	 * Do a quick line-level diff on both strings, then rediff the parts for
	 * greater accuracy.
	 * This speedup can produce non-minimal diffs.
	 * @param {string} text1 Old string to be diffed.
	 * @param {string} text2 New string to be diffed.
	 * @param {number} deadline Time when the diff should be complete by.
	 * @return {!Array.<!diff_match_patch.Diff>} Array of diff tuples.
	 * @private
	 */
	diff_lineMode_: function(text1, text2, deadline) {
	  // Scan the text on a line-by-line basis first.
	  var a = this.diff_linesToChars_(text1, text2);
	  text1 = a.chars1;
	  text2 = a.chars2;
	  var linearray = a.lineArray;

	  var diffs = this.diff_main(text1, text2, false, deadline);

	  // Convert the diff back to original text.
	  this.diff_charsToLines_(diffs, linearray);
	  // Eliminate freak matches (e.g. blank lines)
	  this.diff_cleanupSemantic(diffs);

	  // Rediff any replacement blocks, this time character-by-character.
	  // Add a dummy entry at the end.
	  diffs.push([this.DIFF_EQUAL, '']);
	  var pointer = 0;
	  var count_delete = 0;
	  var count_insert = 0;
	  var text_delete = '';
	  var text_insert = '';
	  while (pointer < diffs.length) {
		switch (diffs[pointer][0]) {
		  case this.DIFF_INSERT:
			count_insert++;
			text_insert += diffs[pointer][1];
			break;
		  case this.DIFF_DELETE:
			count_delete++;
			text_delete += diffs[pointer][1];
			break;
		  case this.DIFF_EQUAL:
			// Upon reaching an equality, check for prior redundancies.
			if (count_delete >= 1 && count_insert >= 1) {
			  // Delete the offending records and add the merged ones.
			  diffs.splice(pointer - count_delete - count_insert,
						   count_delete + count_insert);
			  pointer = pointer - count_delete - count_insert;
			  a = this.diff_main(text_delete, text_insert, false, deadline);
			  for (var j = a.length - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
				diffs.splice(pointer, 0, a[j]);
			  }
			  pointer = pointer + a.length;
			}
			count_insert = 0;
			count_delete = 0;
			text_delete = '';
			text_insert = '';
			break;
		}
		pointer++;
	  }
	  diffs.pop();  // Remove the dummy entry at the end.

	  return diffs;
	},
	/**
	 * Split two texts into an array of strings.  Reduce the texts to a string of
	 * hashes where each Unicode character represents one line.
	 * @param {string} text1 First string.
	 * @param {string} text2 Second string.
	 * @return {{chars1: string, chars2: string, lineArray: !Array.<string>}}
	 *     An object containing the encoded text1, the encoded text2 and
	 *     the array of unique strings.
	 *     The zeroth element of the array of unique strings is intentionally blank.
	 * @private
	 */
	diff_linesToChars_: function(text1, text2) {
	  var lineArray = [];  // e.g. lineArray[4] == 'Hello\n'
	  var lineHash = {};   // e.g. lineHash['Hello\n'] == 4

	  // '\x00' is a valid character, but various debuggers don't like it.
	  // So we'll insert a junk entry to avoid generating a null character.
	  lineArray[0] = '';

	  /**
	   * Split a text into an array of strings.  Reduce the texts to a string of
	   * hashes where each Unicode character represents one line.
	   * Modifies linearray and linehash through being a closure.
	   * @param {string} text String to encode.
	   * @return {string} Encoded string.
	   * @private
	   */
	  function diff_linesToCharsMunge_(text) {
		var chars = '';
		// Walk the text, pulling out a substring for each line.
		// text.split('\n') would would temporarily double our memory footprint.
		// Modifying text would create many large strings to garbage collect.
		var lineStart = 0;
		var lineEnd = -1;
		// Keeping our own length variable is faster than looking it up.
		var lineArrayLength = lineArray.length;
		while (lineEnd < text.length - 1) {
		  lineEnd = text.indexOf('\n', lineStart);
		  if (lineEnd == -1) {
			lineEnd = text.length - 1;
		  }
		  var line = text.substring(lineStart, lineEnd + 1);
		  lineStart = lineEnd + 1;

		  if (lineHash.hasOwnProperty ? lineHash.hasOwnProperty(line) :
			  (lineHash[line] !== undefined)) {
			chars += String.fromCharCode(lineHash[line]);
		  } else {
			chars += String.fromCharCode(lineArrayLength);
			lineHash[line] = lineArrayLength;
			lineArray[lineArrayLength++] = line;
		  }
		}
		return chars;
	  }

	  var chars1 = diff_linesToCharsMunge_(text1);
	  var chars2 = diff_linesToCharsMunge_(text2);
	  return {chars1: chars1, chars2: chars2, lineArray: lineArray};
	},


	/**
	 * Rehydrate the text in a diff from a string of line hashes to real lines of
	 * text.
	 * @param {!Array.<!diff_match_patch.Diff>} diffs Array of diff tuples.
	 * @param {!Array.<string>} lineArray Array of unique strings.
	 * @private
	 */
	diff_charsToLines_: function(diffs, lineArray) {
	  for (var x = 0; x < diffs.length; x++) {
		var chars = diffs[x][1];
		var text = [];
		for (var y = 0; y < chars.length; y++) {
		  text[y] = lineArray[chars.charCodeAt(y)];
		}
		diffs[x][1] = text.join('');
	  }
	},
	type: 'DmpDifferAPI'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>avishek.dalal</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-01-11 09:39:43</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>false</sys_customer_update><sys_id>7dcae1d6db230300a86a5404ce961975</sys_id><sys_mod_count>20</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DmpDifferAPI</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Review Hub" source="x_snc_review_hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Review Hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_7dcae1d6db230300a86a5404ce961975</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>avishek.dalal</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-01-11 14:09:22</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_review_hub.ChangeSetAjax</api_name><client_callable>true</client_callable><description/><name>ChangeSetAjax</name><script><![CDATA[var ChangeSetAjax = Class.create();
ChangeSetAjax.prototype = Object.extendsObject(global.AbstractAjaxProcessor, {
	
	changeSetStateUpdate : function(){
		var changeSetName = this.getParameter('sysparam_changeset')+'';
		var changesetState = this.getParameter('sysparam_state')+'';
		var changeId = this.getParameter('sysparam_change')+'';
		
		var instance = gs.getProperty('x_snc_review_hub.syncinstance');
		
		var localState = 'review_completed'; 
		
		if(changesetState == 'review_failed'){
			localState = 'review_rejected';
		}
		
		var changeRecs = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_changes');
		
		if(changeId){
		    changeRecs.addQuery('sys_id',changeId);
		}else{
			changeRecs.addQuery('change_set.changeset_name',changeSetName);
		}
		changeRecs.query();
		var sys_sync_id = "";
		while(changeRecs.next()){
			//instance = changeRecs.change_set.dev_instance;
			changeRecs.status = localState;
			if(changeId){
				sys_sync_id = changeRecs.dev_change_sysid;
			}
			changeRecs.update();
		}
		
 		var devInstanceHelper = new DevInstanceSyncHelper();
		var result = devInstanceHelper.updateDevChange(changeSetName,changesetState,instance,sys_sync_id);
	
		return JSON.stringify(result);
	},

	getChangeSetsInReview : function(){
		
		try{
			var changeSetsMap = {};
				var personne = this.getParameter('sysparam_personne')+'';
			
				var changeRecs = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_changes');
			    if(personne == 'Developer'){
					changeRecs.addQuery('change_set.created_developer',gs.getUserID());
				}else{
					changeRecs.addQuery('change_set.reviewer',gs.getUserID());
				}
			
		    	changeRecs.addEncodedQuery('statusINreview_in_progress,review_completed');
				changeRecs.orderBy('change_set');
				changeRecs.query();
				
				while(changeRecs.next()){
					var _chSetname = changeRecs.getDisplayValue('change_set') || 'Default';
					
					var _thisChangeSet = {};
						if(!changeSetsMap[_chSetname]){
							
							var changeSet = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_change_set');
							changeSet.addQuery('sys_id',changeRecs.getValue('change_set'));
							changeSet.query();
							changeSet.next();
							
							_thisChangeSet.created_by = changeSet.getDisplayValue('created_developer');
							_thisChangeSet.changed_by = changeSet.getDisplayValue('changed_by');
							_thisChangeSet.instance = changeSet.getDisplayValue('dev_instance');
							_thisChangeSet.reviewer = changeSet.getDisplayValue('reviewer');
							
							_thisChangeSet.files = [];
							changeSetsMap[_chSetname] = _thisChangeSet;
						} else {
							_thisChangeSet = changeSetsMap[_chSetname];
						}
						
						var _thisFileMeta = {};
							_thisFileMeta.file_name = changeRecs.getValue('file_name');
							_thisFileMeta.reviewer = changeRecs.getDisplayValue('reviewer');
							_thisFileMeta.status = changeRecs.getValue('status');
							_thisFileMeta.developer = changeRecs.getDisplayValue('developer');
							_thisFileMeta.type = changeRecs.getValue('type');
							_thisFileMeta.change_id = changeRecs.getValue('sys_id');
							_thisFileMeta.file_id = changeRecs.getValue('fileid');
							_thisChangeSet.files.push(_thisFileMeta);
							
						}
						return JSON.stringify(changeSetsMap);
						
					}catch(e){
						gs.info("Exception in getting changesets in review "+e);
					}
				},
	
	getXMLDifferCode: function() {
		var change_id = this.getParameter('sysparam_changeid')+'';		
		var result = {};
		
		var gr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_changes');
		if(gr.get(change_id)){
			
			var xmlDoc = new XMLDocument2();
			xmlDoc.parseXML(gr.payload);
			var srcScript = gr.getValue('payload');
			if(srcScript) {
				var tableNode = xmlDoc.getFirstNode('//sys_class_name');
				var tableName = tableNode.getTextContent();

				var recordNode = xmlDoc.getFirstNode('//sys_id');
				var recordId = recordNode.getTextContent();

				var targetInstance = gr.change_set.target_instance;

				// get the parent scrpt
				var response = this.getTargetRecord(targetInstance,tableName,recordId);
				var targetScript = "";

				if(response && response.result && response.result.length > 0){
					targetScript = response.result[0].script;
				}
				
				result = this._diffPayloads(srcScript, targetScript);				
			}
			
		}
		
	   return result;
	},
	
	getDifferCode : function(){
		gs.info("Get Diff Code","Review-Hub");
		var change_id = this.getParameter('sysparam_changeid')+'';		
		var result = {};
		
		var gr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_changes');
		if(gr.get(change_id)){
			
			var xmlDoc = new XMLDocument2();
			xmlDoc.parseXML(gr.payload);
			var scriptNode = xmlDoc.getFirstNode('//script');
			if(scriptNode){
				var srcScript = scriptNode.getTextContent();
				var tableNode = xmlDoc.getFirstNode('//sys_class_name');
				var tableName = tableNode.getTextContent();

				var recordNode = xmlDoc.getFirstNode('//sys_id');
				var recordId = recordNode.getTextContent();

				var targetInstance = gr.change_set.target_instance;

				// get the parent scrpt
				var response = this.getTargetRecord(targetInstance,tableName,recordId);
				var targetScript = "";

				if(response && response.result && response.result.length > 0){
					targetScript = response.result[0].script;
				}

				result = this._diffPayloads(srcScript, targetScript);							
			}
			
		}
		
	   return result;
		
	},
	
	getPayloads: function() {
		var change_id = this.getParameter('sysparam_changeid')+'';		
		var result = {};
		
		var gr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_changes');
		if(gr.get(change_id)){
			result['source'] = gr.getValue('payload');
			
			var targetInstance = gr.change_set?gr.change_set.target_instance:"";
			if(targetInstance) {
				var xmlDoc = new XMLDocument2();
				xmlDoc.parseXML(gr.payload);

				var tableNode = xmlDoc.getFirstNode('//sys_class_name');
				var tableName = tableNode.getTextContent();

				var recordNode = xmlDoc.getFirstNode('//sys_id');
				var recordId = recordNode.getTextContent();
				gs.info('calling getTargetRecord = ' + targetInstance + ':' + tableName + ':' + recordId);
				var response = this.getTargetRecord(targetInstance,tableName,recordId);
				gs.info('Target Record payload = '); 
				gs.info(JSON.stringify(response));
				if(response && response.result && response.result.length > 0){
					result['target'] = response.result[0];
				}
			}
		}	
		return JSON.stringify(result);
	}, 
	
	diffPayloads : function() {
		var srcPayload = this.getParameter('srcPayload');
		var targetPayload = this.getParameter('targetPayload');
		return this._diffPayloads(srcPayload, targetPayload);
	},
	
	_diffPayloads : function(srcPayload, targetPayload) {
		var differ = new DifferUtil();
		var feed = "";
		if(targetPayload) {
			feed = differ.feed(srcPayload,targetPayload);
		}else {
			feed = differ.feed(srcPayload,srcPayload);
		}		       

		return JSON.stringify(feed.get());
	},
	
	getTargetRecord : function(instance,tableName,recordId){
		gs.info("Inside Get Target Record");
		try {
			var username = gs.getProperty('x_snc_review_hub.username');
			var password = gs.getProperty('x_snc_review_hub.password');
			
			var request = new sn_ws.RESTMessageV2();
			var endPoint = "https://" + instance + ".service-now.com/api/now/table/"+tableName;
			gs.info("endPoint "+endPoint);
			request.setEndpoint(endPoint);
			var query = "sys_id="+recordId;
			gs.info("query "+query);
			request.setQueryParameter("sysparm_query",query);
			
			request.setHttpMethod('GET');
			
			request.setBasicAuth(username,password);
			gs.info("username: "+username+ "- Pass: "+password);
			request.setRequestHeader("Accept","application/json");
			
			var response = request.execute();
			var responseBody = response.getBody();
			var httpStatus = response.getStatusCode();
			gs.info("Status: "+httpStatus);
			if(httpStatus == 200){
				return JSON.parse(responseBody);
			}
		}
		catch(ex) {
			gs.info(ex);
		}
	},
	
	
	setCommentFile : function(){
		try{
			var change_id = this.getParameter('sysparam_changeid')+'';
			var fileId = this.getParameter('sysparam_fileid')+'';
			
			var lineNumber = this.getParameter('sysparam_linenum')+'';
			var message = this.getParameter('sysparam_message')+'';
			//var user = this.getParameter('sysparam_user')+'';

			var commentsRec = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_comments');
			commentsRec.initialize();

			commentsRec.changeid = change_id;
			commentsRec.linenumber = lineNumber;
			commentsRec.commentedby = gs.getUserID();
			commentsRec.description = message;
			commentsRec.fileid = fileId;

			var sys_id = commentsRec.insert();
		
            var result = {};
			return JSON.stringify(result);
		}catch(e){
			
		}
		
	},
	
	getCommentsForUser : function(){
		try{
			
			var userComments = {};
			var comments = [];
			
			var commentsRec = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_comments');
			commentsRec.addQuery('commentedby',gs.getUserID());
			commentsRec.addQuery('read_comment',false);
			commentsRec.query();
			
			while(commentsRec.next()){
				var comment = {};
				
				comment.user = commentsRec.getDisplayValue('commentedby');
				comment.desc = commentsRec.getValue('description');
				comment.changeId = commentsRec.getValue('changeid');
				comment.changeName = commentsRec.getDisplayValue('changeid');
				comment.commentedOn = commentsRec.getValue('sys_created_on');
				comment.commentId = commentsRec.getValue('sys_id');
				
				comments.push(comment);
			}
			
		    userComments.comments =  comments;
			
			return JSON.stringify(userComments);
			
		}catch(e){
			
		}
	},
	
	getCommentsforFile : function(){
		try{
			var change_id = this.getParameter('sysparam_changeid')+'';
			//var fileid = this.getParameter('sysparam_fileid')+'';
			var comments = {};

			// query the comments related to file
			var commentsRec = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_comments');
			commentsRec.addQuery('changeid',change_id);
			//commentsRec.addQuery('fileid',fileid);
			commentsRec.query();

			while(commentsRec.next()){
				var file = commentsRec.getValue('changeid');
				//var file = commentsRec.getValue('fileid');
				var _line = commentsRec.getValue('linenumber');
				var _user = commentsRec.getDisplayValue('commentedby');
				var _description = commentsRec.getValue('description');

				if(!comments[file])
				comments[file] = {};
				if(!comments[file][_line])
					comments[file][_line] = [];
				comments[file][_line].push({
					"user": _user,
					"message": _description
				});
			}

			return JSON.stringify(comments);
		}catch(e){
			
		}
		
	},
	
	setCommentAsRead : function(){
		//read_comment
		try{
			var result = {};
			
			var commentID = this.getParameter('sysparam_commentid')+'';
			
			if(commentID){
				var commentsRec = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_comments');
				commentsRec.get(commentID);
				commentsRec.read_comment = true;
				commentsRec.update();
			}
			result.success = "true";
			
			return JSON.stringify(result);
			
		}catch(e){
			
		}
	},
	
	getUserDetails : function(){
		try{
			 var userName = gs.getUserDisplayName();
			//return JSON.stringify(userName);
			var userInfo = {
				name : userName
			};
			
			return JSON.stringify(userInfo);
		}catch(e){
			
		}
	},
	
	getChangeReviewer : function(){
		var change_id = this.getParameter('sysparam_changeid')+'';		
		var result = {};
		var reviewer = {};
		
		var gr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_changes');
		gr.addQuery('sys_id',change_id);
	    gr.query();
		
		if(gr.next()){
			reviewer.changed_by = gr.getDisplayValue('developer');
			reviewer.reviewer = gr.getDisplayValue('reviewer');
		}
		result.reviewer = reviewer;
		
		return JSON.stringify(result);
	},
				
  type: 'ChangeSetAjax'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>haribabu.garbhana</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-02-02 10:21:20</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>e21a8bdddbc01f00a86a5404ce961960</sys_id><sys_mod_count>124</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ChangeSetAjax</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Review Hub" source="x_snc_review_hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Review Hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_e21a8bdddbc01f00a86a5404ce961960</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>haribabu.garbhana</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-05-29 06:40:25</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_review_hub.ReviewSetUtil</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>Get Review Set Details to the client side</description><name>ReviewSetUtil</name><script><![CDATA[var ReviewSetUtil = Class.create();
ReviewSetUtil.prototype = {
	
	initialize: function(){},

    fetchReviewSetByDeveloper: function(_user){

        var updateSets = [];
        var TABLE_NAME = 'x_snc_review_hub_review_set';
        var query = 'u_developer='+_user;

        updateSets = this._getUpdateSetDetails(TABLE_NAME,query);
        return updateSets;
    },

    _getUpdateSetDetails: function(TABLE_NAME,QUERY){

        var updateSets = [];
        var gr = new GlideRecord(TABLE_NAME);
        gr.addEncodedQuery(QUERY);
        gr.query();

        while(gr.next()){
            var updateSet = {
                'name': gr.u_name + '',
                'story': gr.u_story + '',
                'progress': gr.u_progress + '',
                'instance': gr.u_review_instance + '',
                'developer': gr.u_developer + '',
                'sprint': gr.u_sprint + '',
                'sys_id': gr.u_review_set_sys_id + '',
                'reviewers': []
            };

            updateSets.push(updateSet);
        }


    },

    type: 'ReviewSetUtil'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>souvik</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-01-08 09:05:26</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>false</sys_customer_update><sys_id>ddd64699db67cf00a86a5404ce96193f</sys_id><sys_mod_count>4</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ReviewSetUtil</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Review Hub" source="x_snc_review_hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Review Hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_ddd64699db67cf00a86a5404ce96193f</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>souvik</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-01-10 11:42:54</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_review_hub.DifferUtil</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>Utility API to interact with Google's DMP Library to generate diffs.
Internally uses DmpDifferApi Script Include</description><name>DifferUtil</name><script><![CDATA[var DifferUtil = Class.create();
DifferUtil.prototype = {
	baseCode: null,
	newCode: null,
	diffs: null,
	
	MARKER_INSERT_START: null,
	MARKER_INSERT_END: null,
	MARKER_DELETE_START: null,
	MARKER_DELETE_END: null,
	
    initialize: function() {
		
    },
	feed: function(baseCode, newCode){
		if(typeof baseCode !== "string" || typeof newCode !== "string")
			return this.verbose_template(true, 0, null);
		if(!baseCode || !newCode)
			return this.verbose_template(true, 1, null);
		if(baseCode === "" && newCode === "")
			return this.verbose_template(true, 2, null);
		this._setupMarkers();
		this.baseCode = baseCode;
		this.newCode = newCode;
		this.diffs = null;
		var _get = this.get();
		return {
			"get": function(){
				return _get;
			}
		};
	},
	_setupMarkers: function(){
		var randomSalt = 1;
		this.MARKER_INSERT_START = '<ins>';
		this.MARKER_INSERT_END = '</ins>';
		this.MARKER_DELETE_START = '<del>';
		this.MARKER_DELETE_END = '</del>';
	},
	verbose_template: function(isError, errorCode, successRaw){
		var template = {
			error: {},
			result: null
		};
		if(isError){
			template.error.code = "ERR-" + errorCode;
			template.error.message = this.error(errorCode);
		}else{
			template.result = successRaw;
		}
		return template;
	},
	error: function(code){
		code = code.toString();
		var _errors = {};
		_errors["0"] = "invalid datatype";
		_errors["1"] = "missing parameter";
		_errors["2"] = "empty data";
		_errors["3"] = "fatal error";
		_errors["4"] = "invalid function call";
		if(_errors[code])
			return _errors[code].toUpperCase();
		return _errors["2"].toUpperCase();
	},
	_codify: function(code, verbose){
		var splittedCodes = code.split("\n");
		var line = 1;
		var codes = [];
		for(var i=0; i<splittedCodes.length; i++){
			codes.push({
				line_number: line++,
				code_text: splittedCodes[i]
			});
		}
		if(verbose)
			return this.verbose_template(false, -1, codes);
		return codes;
	},
	_raw_differences: function(verbose){
		if(this.diffs !== null)
			return this.diffs;
		try{
			var dmpDiffer = new DmpDifferAPI();
			var diffs = dmpDiffer.diff_main(this.baseCode, this.newCode);
			dmpDiffer.diff_cleanupSemantic(diffs);
			this.diffs = diffs;
			if(verbose)
				return this.verbose_template(false, -1, diffs);
			return diffs;
		}catch(e){
			return this.verbose_template(true, 3, null);
		}
	},
	_smartWrapText: function(text, token){
		token = token.toUpperCase();
		var _start = this["MARKER_" + token + "_START"];
		var _end = this["MARKER_" + token + "_END"];
		
		var regex = new RegExp(_start, "g");
		var starts = regex.exec(text);
		regex = new RegExp(_end, "g");
		var ends = regex.exec(text);

		if(starts !== null && ends === null)
			text = text + _end;
		if(starts === null && ends !== null)
			text = _start + text;
		if(starts !== null && ends !== null){
			if(starts.length > ends.length){
				text = text + _end;
			}else if(starts.length < ends.length){
				text = _start + text;
			}
		}
		return text;
	},
	_clearScript: function(text){
		var token = "INSERT";
		var _start = this["MARKER_" + token + "_START"];
		var _end = this["MARKER_" + token + "_END"];
		var regex = new RegExp(_start, "g");
		text = text.replace(regex, "");
		regex = new RegExp(_end, "g");
		text = text.replace(regex, "");
		
		token = "DELETE";
		text = this._smartWrapText(text, token);
		_start = this["MARKER_" + token + "_START"];
		_end = this["MARKER_" + token + "_END"];
		regex = new RegExp(_start + '(.*?)' + _end, 'gm');
		var scriplets = text.match(regex);
		if(scriplets !== null){
			for(var i=0; i<scriplets.length; i++){
				text = text.replace(scriplets[i], "");
			}
		}
		return text;
	},
	_getDifference: function(text){
		text = this._smartWrapText(text, "insert");
		text = this._smartWrapText(text, "delete");
		return text;
	},
	diff: function(codeLet1, codeLet2, verbose){
		var mergedCodes = [], i = 0;
		var diffs = this._raw_differences(false);
		//gs.info(diffs);
		var diffString = "";
		for(i=0; i<diffs.length; i++){
			var mode = diffs[i][0];
			var text = diffs[i][1];
			if(mode === 1){
				diffString += this.MARKER_INSERT_START + text + this.MARKER_INSERT_END;
			}
			else if(mode === -1){
				diffString += this.MARKER_DELETE_START + text + this.MARKER_DELETE_END;
			}else{
				diffString += text;
			}
		}
		var diffStringSplitted = diffString.split('\n');
		for(i=0; i<diffStringSplitted.length; i++){
			var _diffText = diffStringSplitted[i];
			if(_diffText.indexOf(this.MARKER_INSERT_START) >= 0 || _diffText.indexOf(this.MARKER_INSERT_END) >= 0 || _diffText.indexOf(this.MARKER_DELETE_START) >= 0 || _diffText.indexOf(this.MARKER_DELETE_END) >= 0){
				mergedCodes.push({
					line_number: (i+1),
					script: this._clearScript(_diffText),
					compare: true,
					difference: this._getDifference(_diffText)
				});
			}else{
				mergedCodes.push({
					line_number: (i+1),
					script: _diffText,
					compare: false,
					difference: null
				});
			}
		}
		if(verbose)
			return this.verbose_template(false, -1, mergedCodes);
		return mergedCodes;
	},
	get: function(){
		var api = {};
		api.raw_differences = this._raw_differences(true);
		api.codify_base = this._codify(this.baseCode, true);
		api.codify_latest = this._codify(this.newCode, true);
		api.compare = this.diff(this.baseCode, this.newCode, true);
		
		return api;
	},
	
	
    type: 'DifferUtil'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>avishek.dalal</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-01-11 10:36:02</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>0e383952db630300a86a5404ce961995</sys_id><sys_mod_count>41</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DifferUtil</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Review Hub" source="x_snc_review_hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Review Hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_0e383952db630300a86a5404ce961995</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>haribabu.garbhana</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-05-14 09:33:27</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

RestAPI.prototype = {

	},

		try{
			var connect = new ConnectAPI('GET',restParam);
			return connect.response;
		}
		catch(err){
			gs.error("Error executing GET method: "+err.getMessage());
			throw new Error("Error executing GET method: "+err.getMessage());
		}
    },

    },

    put: function(restParam){

        try{

		}
		catch(err){
			gs.error("Error executing PUT method: "+err.getMessage());
			throw new Error("Error executing PUT method: "+err.getMessage());
		}
    },

	},
	
    type: 'RestAPI'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>souvik</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-01-08 11:45:02</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>d12cca5ddb67cf00a86a5404ce961952</sys_id><sys_mod_count>28</sys_mod_count><sys_name>RestAPI</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Review Hub" source="x_snc_review_hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Review Hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_d12cca5ddb67cf00a86a5404ce961952</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>haribabu.garbhana</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-05-18 10:07:36</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_review_hub.ReviewHubFilesRetriever</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>ReviewHubFilesRetriever</name><script><![CDATA[var ReviewHubFilesRetriever = Class.create();
ReviewHubFilesRetriever.prototype = {
	initialize: function() {
	},
	
	getUpdateSetFiles: function() {
		var requestParam = {};
			requestParam.url ="https://surfdev5.service-now.com/api/now/table/sys_update_xml";
			requestParam.instance = "surfdev5";
			requestParam.sysparm_query ="update_set=52684847dbac03803f377bedae961978";
			requestParam.sysparm_fields ="type,target_name,payload";
			var body = new RestAPI().get(requestParam);
			var result = (JSON.parse(body.response)).result;
			for (var i=0; i<result.length; i++){
				gs.info("Type: "+result[i].type);
				gs.info("Target Name: "+result[i].target_name);
				gs.info("payload: "+result[i].payload);
				var gr = new GlideRecord("x_snc_review_hub_review_files");
				gr.initialize();
				gr.u_file_name = result[i].target_name;
				gr.u_payload = result[i].payload;
				gr.u_type = result[i].type;
				gr.insert();
			}
		},
		
		getPayloadScript: function(reviewfileId){
			var script='';
			var gr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_review_hub_review_files');
			gr.get(reviewfileId);
			gr.query();
			if(gr.next()){
				var str = gr.u_payload;
				var res = new ReviewHubUtil().parse(str);
				script = res.script;
			}
			return script;
		},
		
		type: 'ReviewHubFilesRetriever'
	};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sreelakshmi.balanagu</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-01-09 08:47:28</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>false</sys_customer_update><sys_id>ebfe3a61dba38f007236d9f0ce96193d</sys_id><sys_mod_count>18</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ReviewHubFilesRetriever</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Review Hub" source="x_snc_review_hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Review Hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_ebfe3a61dba38f007236d9f0ce96193d</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sreelakshmi.balanagu</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-01-22 12:02:47</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_review_hub.ReviewHubUtil</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>Parsing XML nodes</description><name>ReviewHubUtil</name><script><![CDATA[var ReviewHubUtil = Class.create();
ReviewHubUtil.prototype = {
	initialize: function() {
	},
	parse: function(xmlString) {
		var doc = new XMLDocument2();
		doc.parseXML(xmlString);
		var recordNode = doc.getNode('record_update').getFirstChild();
		// sys_documentation records have an extra node,
		// also named sys_documentation, because why not
		if (recordNode.getNodeName() === 'sys_documentation'){
			recordNode = recordNode.getFirstChild();
		}
		var recordIterator = recordNode.getChildNodeIterator();
		var result = {}, n;
			while (recordIterator.hasNext()) {
				n = recordIterator.next();
				result[n.getNodeName()] = n.getTextContent();
			}
			return result;
		},
		
		type: 'ReviewHubUtil'
	};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sreelakshmi.balanagu</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-01-22 11:50:20</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>false</sys_customer_update><sys_id>48343ef1dbf38700a86a5404ce961975</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ReviewHubUtil</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Review Hub" source="x_snc_review_hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Review Hub">bd29155ddbe3cf00a86a5404ce961990</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_48343ef1dbf38700a86a5404ce961975</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sreelakshmi.balanagu</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-01-22 11:50:20</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

DevInstanceSyncHelper.prototype = {
	initialize: function() {
	},
	updateDevChange:function(changeSetName,state,instance,changeId){
		var requestParam = {};
		if(changeSetName){
			requestParam.url = "https://"+instance+".service-now.com"+global.ReviewHubConstants.REST_API;	
		}else{
			requestParam.url = "https://"+instance+".service-now.com"+global.ReviewHubConstants.REST_API_CHANGE;
		}
		
		requestParam.instance = instance;
		requestParam.content_type ="application/json";
        
		var reqBody = {};
		if(changeSetName){
			reqBody.name = changeSetName;
		}else{
			reqBody.sys_id = changeId+'';
		}
		reqBody.state = state;
		
		requestParam.requestBody = JSON.stringify(reqBody);
		var body = new x_snc_review_hub.RestAPI().post(requestParam);
		return body;
	},
				
	type: 'DevInstanceSyncHelper'
